d><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where can a level 60 paladin MT on raids</span><hr size=1> We pretty much always use a warrior to MT at our raids, the only times I would MT would be if there were no warriors present.  However in general I'd answer your question by telling you what things to look for:<br><br>- Mobs on the lower end of melee damage (max hit or DB/DI methods to measure that)<br>- Mobs that don't flurry<br>- Most that are slowable<br><br>Those would be to identify mobs that a Paladin *can* tank.  There is no set cutoff for how much melee damage, because it will depend on how many clerics, healers, debuffers, slowers, etc. you have available, not just the mob's profile.<br><br>As far as what a Paladin would be better suited to tank, I'd primarly look for:<br><br>- Mobs that make it difficult to control aggro, for example mobs that slow the MT, or mobs that are particularly sensitive to going after healers--Paladins will have an easier time holding aggro.<br>- Mobs that you need to kill quickly and you need to go full guns blazing from the start--if letting the MT build up aggro for a while won't work, Paladins can do a better job out-aggroing chain nukers from the start, so casters can start right away.<br><br>As far as specific mobs I'll leave that to others since as I stated my guild always uses warriors if we have them available, at least so far. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Duke Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uazzigothghul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azzigoth Ghul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protecto