<br><br>Anything slowable (and that's a lot of high end mobs), it's a different story.  <br><br>Mobs which make aggro hard to hold are ideal.<br><br>Also encounters where you need to get aggro NOW - eg. when you are pulling a lot of mobs and you need them all tanked now not in a minutes time when all your Clerics and shaman are dead.<br><br>If you need to tank a mob for a long time without a lot of backup - obviously a Paladin is going to stay in there a lot longer than a warrior.  Not all mobs in high end encounters need CHeals every 0.0002 of a second on the tank...<br><br>Specific examples.. well DT mobs, Glyphed, Shei - aggro transfer is smooth with hybrids.<br><br>Lady Nev? in ToV.. the one with the irritating spin AoE.  Much easier for a hybrid to hold aggro.<br><br>There are plenty more.  Just have to break out of the worldrevolvesaroundwarriors mentality... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulukrathien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lukrathien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 9:18:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=606.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where can a level 60 paladin MT on raids</span><hr size=1> Sometimes when aggro bounces on a flurry drake or a warrior dies for some reason I tank it. :P I couldn't without slow the whole time though probably. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueasirok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>easirok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/29/02 9:42:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladin